---
description: Rigorous structural code quality review. Run as design gate (after RED, before writing code) and code gate (after tests pass).
alwaysApply: false
---

Run twice per TDD slice: **design gate** (after RED, before GREEN) and **code gate** (after GREEN/REFACTOR). Block on any approval blocker before continuing.

**Five criteria:**
1. **File size** — 1,000-line files require decomposition, not growth.
2. **Spaghetti** — Reject ad-hoc conditionals and special cases in unrelated flows.
3. **Abstractions** — Reject thin wrappers and identity layers. Every layer must earn its place.
4. **Types** — Prefer explicit typed models; flag unnecessary optionality, casts, and loose shapes.
5. **Canonical reuse** — Logic in one place; flag duplicates and feature logic leaking into shared code.

**Blockers** (must resolve before proceeding):
- Visible simpler restructuring left undone
- File pushed past 1,000 lines
- Ad-hoc branching in existing flows
- Thin wrappers or cast-heavy contracts introduced
- Feature checks scattered across shared code
